<% content_for :title, "Privacy" %>
<main class="pt-page">
  <section class="pt-hero">
    <div class="container-xl">
      <div class="pt-eyebrow">Legal</div>
      <h1 class="pt-h1">Privacy</h1>
      <p class="pt-lede">
        PriceTracker is a student project. We try to collect as little data as
        possible. This page describes what we store, why, and how to request
        deletion.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container-xl pt-content">
    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Account info:</strong> your email address, an optional profile photo (Active Storage), and a hashed (bcrypt) password.</li>
      <li><strong>Products you track:</strong> the URLs, names, images, categories, and descriptions of products you add.</li>
      <li><strong>Price history:</strong> prices and store names for the products you've added, recorded over time.</li>
      <li><strong>Session data:</strong> a signed cookie identifying your active session.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do <strong>not</strong> use third-party analytics or advertising trackers.</p>

    <h2>How we use it</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To let you sign in and keep you signed in.</li>
      <li>To show you the products and price history you've added.</li>
      <li>To fetch updated prices from supported retailers on your behalf.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not sell your data. We do not share your data with third parties except as required to operate the app (e.g., the hosting provider).</p>

    <h2>How we store it</h2>
    <p>
      Data is stored in a PostgreSQL database hosted alongside the app.
      Passwords are never stored in plaintext.
    </p>

    <h2>How to delete your account</h2>
    <p>
      Signed-in users can delete their account immediately from
      <%= link_to "Account settings", account_path %> (password or email confirmation required).
      This permanently removes your products, price records, folders, and sessions.
    </p>

    <h2>Questions or concerns</h2>
    <p>
      We do not list team member email addresses on this page. For privacy-related
      questions, open an issue on our
      <a href="https://github.com/NU-CS-Software-Studio-Spring-26/project-smart-shopping-list/issues"
         target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Issues page</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      This is a class project under active development. If this policy
      changes meaningfully we'll update this page and note it in the project's
      <a href="https://github.com/NU-CS-Software-Studio-Spring-26/project-smart-shopping-list"
         target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">CHANGELOG</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</main>
